quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  19,39,"O Muhammad, forewarn them about the Day of intense regret when this matter will be decided, even though at present they are paying no heed and do not believe"
  19,40,"Ultimately, all things will perish and it is We, Who will inherit the earth and all that is on it, and to Us shall they return"
  19,41,"Relate to them the story of Abraham from the Book (The Qur'an), he was a truthful Prophet"
  19,42,"Remember when he said to his father: \"O my father! Why do you worship something that can neither hear nor see, nor yet profit you in any way"
  19,43,"O my father! I have been given some knowledge which has not come to you, so follow me: Iâ€™ll guide you to the Right Way"
  19,44,"O my father! Do not worship Satan: for Satan is disobedient to the Compassionate (Allah)"
  19,45,"O my father! I fear that a punishment of the Beneficent may afflict you, and you may become a friend of the Satan"
  19,46,"His father replied: \"How dare you renounce my gods O Abraham? If you do not stop this folly, I will indeed stone you to death: so begone from my house this very moment"
  19,47,"Abraham said: \"Peace be upon you: I will pray to my Lord for your forgiveness, surely He is ever Kind to me"
  19,48,"I am leaving you and those whom you invoke besides Allah: I will call upon my Lord and I am sure my prayers to my Lord will not be ignored"
  19,49,"So when he left them and the deities whom they worshipped besides Allah, We granted him descendants like Isaac and Jacob, and We made each of them a Prophet"
  19,50,We bestowed on them Our Mercy and We granted them the honor of being mentioned with true high respect
  19,51,"Relate to them the story of Moses in the Book; surely he was a chosen man and was a Messenger, a Prophet"